cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper discusses the vulnerability of deep neural networks to adversarial attacks and proposes enhanced attacks on defensively distilled DNNs. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves techniques such as epsilon-neighborhood attack and region-based attack, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
